reviews.review_text:
I could pay you back, with one good hand. Something to be said for the rough & tumble BIKER's that preceded the Touch of Grey madness
Jerry gets in some sweet licks during Sugaree
He not busy being born
Is busy dying..
Context. 1) This was Chinese New Years so there was already some music preceding the boys.                       
2) I would not want to be doing a concert after my dog died, so give Weir a break!
I would still consider these comeback shows with      
3) Garcia's diabetic coma not that far in the rear view.
The Dead lived their lives out on stage so you really do have to take it all in stride. For me some of these gritty nights endeared me to the band more than when they were firing on all cylinders. How often does life become difficult and cumbersome? 
If you went to enough shows you had to have seen your share of hard times?
Having not a dime to my name and then remembering after the show that I had an extra ticket in my pocket that could have brought in some cash (at face value) plus gotten somebody into the show, Auggghhh!
Yeah, this is slow going but if you stuck around long enough by 1989 they were killing it just about every night.
A very beautiful B.E. Women.
Rugged Cassidy--Fast &quick-- Don't Ease
SCARLET >FIRE no need to rate it or grade it or try to explain it or help me relate to it. 'Forget your weakness and dance, forget your sickness and dance'
Got to make it from Begonia's to the Mountain
He would not forgive you if you will not take the chance..
It's alright, I will still sing you love songs..
4) Gung Ho Fat Chow!
- Rough at the beginning, but mostly excellent!
